</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C3172011A335FFC8FD76FE81FCEFFDD9" blockId="17.[714,1247,352,532]" pageId="17" pageNumber="72">
This species resembles 
<taxonomicName id="04A85B92A335FFC8FC7BFE80FB08FEB1" box="[1001,1180,352,379]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Disperis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="17" pageNumber="72" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hildebrandtii">
<emphasis id="F1DCFC03A335FFC8FC7BFE80FB08FEB1" box="[1001,1180,352,379]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="72">D. hildebrandtii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in its habit. It is readily distinguished by the terminal appendage of its lip which is stalked not sessile and by the indumentum of that appendage which lacks the vesicular hairs that are characteristic of 
<taxonomicName id="04A85B92A335FFC8FD58FE19FCE1FDDE" box="[714,885,505,532]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Disperis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="17" pageNumber="72" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hildebrandtii">
<emphasis id="F1DCFC03A335FFC8FD58FE19FCE1FDDE" box="[714,885,505,532]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="72">D. hildebrandtii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
